From 84ce8b62e8628baabb05b321b4a225bdb75b9f28 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Feb 2021 21:35:21 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 06/15] uio: Inform UIO no-reset-line to users

Introduce new -EOPNOTSUPP return value for UIO devices
without reset line.

Signed-off-by: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
---
 drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
index 9870222600d9..ffaebaa49d1e 100644
--- a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
+++ b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
@@ -278,6 +278,9 @@ static int priv_get_rst(struct uio_info *info)
 	struct uio_pdrv_genirq_platdata *priv = info->priv;
 	int status;
 
+	if (!priv->rst)
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
+
 	status = reset_control_status(priv->rst);
 	dev_dbg(&priv->pdev->dev, "Get reset state 0x%x\n", status);
 
-- 
